other_tests.findings: Marked gallbladder wall thickening, with hyperemic wall; multiple shadowing gallstones; positive sonographic sign; liver adjacent to gallbladder fossa hypoechoic, likely reactive/edema; no intra- or extra-hepatic biliary dilatation; 1.5 x 2.0 x 1.9 cm hyperechoic lesion in the right lobe of the liver; 2.6 x 1.7 x 2.1 cm hypoechoic structure in the right kidney, likely a cyst.
